# Voltig - Project Structure Documentation

## Overview
Voltig is a full-stack workflow automation platform built with Go backend and React frontend. It provides a visual workflow builder, execution engine, and management dashboard for creating and running automated workflows.

## Architecture

```
voltig/
├── backend/          # Go API server and workflow engine
├── frontend/         # React/TypeScript web application
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Makefile
└── README.md
```

## Backend Structure (Go)

### Core Application
- **`main.go`** - Application entry point and server initialization
- **`go.mod/go.sum`** - Go module dependencies

### Internal Packages

#### Configuration & Infrastructure
```
internal/
├── config/           # Application configuration
│   └── config.go
├── db/              # Database layer
│   ├── db.go        # Database connection and setup
│   ├── queries/     # SQL queries (SQLC)
│   └── sqlc/        # Generated Go code from SQL
├── logger/          # Logging utilities
├── middleware/      # HTTP middleware
└── route/           # Route definitions
```

#### API Layer
```
internal/handlers/
├── agent_handler.go      # Agent management endpoints
├── auth_handler.go       # Authentication endpoints
├── execution_handler.go  # Workflow execution endpoints
├── health_handler.go     # Health check endpoints
├── integration_handle.go # Integration management
├── user_handler.go       # User management
└── workflow_handler.go   # Workflow CRUD operations
```

#### Business Logic
```
internal/services/
├── agent_service.go      # Agent business logic
├── auth_service.go       # Authentication logic
├── execution_service.go  # Execution management
├── integration_service.go # Integration handling
├── user_service.go       # User management
